<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Secretary of State to the
                            Embassy in Cuba</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v02</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d384</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">384</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-05-12T17:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-05-12T17:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-12T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-12T17:00:00-05:00" n="384" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d384">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.61351/5–1249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Cuba</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-12T18:00:00-04:00">May 12, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>197. Tentative agreement reached today with reps Cuban Sugar Inst for
                    simultaneous purchase 400,000 long tons sugar by <gloss target="#t_CCC1">CCC</gloss> and <pb facs="0646" n="630" xml:id="pg_630"/> 350,000 long tons
                    by Brit. Agreement which will also govern terms Brit purchase provides: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>250,000 long tons, including 5 CC parcels already shipped, at four
                            cents per pound for shipment Príor July 1.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Balance to be shipped rate 100,000 long tons per month subsequent July
                            1 will be priced according average world spot price Cuban sugar New York
                            market prevailing during month of shipment.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Cuban Govt will release 250,000 long tons for free world
                            market.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_CCC1">CCC</gloss> officials, Sir William Book rep Brit Food
                    Ministry, and Cuban negotiators pleased over agreement. Cuban reps endeavoring
                    clear agreement with Prío by phone today and if he approves, press release will
                    probably be issued here tomorrow.<note n="1" xml:id="d384fn1">Airgram 646, May
                        13, from Habana (not printed), transmitted the texts of comments made by
                        President Prío and Agriculture Minister Perez on the conclusion of the sugar
                        agreement (837.61351/5–1349).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
